WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:54.930
Enter: Captain Usopp

31
00:01:56.930 --> 00:02:00.640
It'd be reckless to head straight
to the Grand Line like this!

32
00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:06.770
Yeah, we should get some meat first.

33
00:02:07.730 --> 00:02:10.440
We can't just eat fruit every day...

34
00:02:10.440 --> 00:02:11.940
We need some booze too!

35
00:02:12.700 --> 00:02:14.530
What're you talking about?!

36
00:02:16.530 --> 00:02:17.660
Knock it off!

37
00:02:17.660 --> 00:02:21.620
The Grand Line is the most
dangerous sea in the world!

38
00:02:21.620 --> 00:02:25.920
It's crawling with fierce pirates
who are also after the One Piece!

39
00:02:25.920 --> 00:02:28.170
And you can bet they
have formidable ships!

40
00:02:28.170 --> 00:02:29.590
We need more crewmates, too.

41
00:02:29.960 --> 00:02:33.930
From the lack of crew members,
to the lack of equipment,

42
00:02:33.930 --> 00:02:36.300
there's no way we can
survive like this!

43
00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:38.680
Yeah, we need a cook.

44
00:02:38.680 --> 00:02:39.890
And a musician.

45
00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:41.270
A musician?!

46
00:02:42.890 --> 00:02:44.730
What an idiot...

47
00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:50.230
There's a populated island
a little south of here.

48
00:02:50.230 --> 00:02:54.780
Let's hope we can get our hands
on a real ship there...

49
00:02:55.150 --> 00:02:57.240
Alright! Time to get some meat!

50
00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:05.670
Everyone! We're doomed!

51
00:03:05.670 --> 00:03:08.250
The pirates are coming!

52
00:03:08.250 --> 00:03:10.710
Pirates! Pirates!

53
00:03:10.710 --> 00:03:13.670
The pirates are coming!

54
00:03:13.670 --> 00:03:16.340
Run for your lives!

55
00:03:16.340 --> 00:03:18.720
Pirates!

56
00:03:18.720 --> 00:03:22.180
Run for your lives!

57
00:03:22.180 --> 00:03:24.060
We're doomed!

58
00:03:26.980 --> 00:03:28.600
The pirates...!

59
00:03:30.900 --> 00:03:33.110
The pirates are...

60
00:03:33.610 --> 00:03:37.360
Usopp
A Village Youngster

61
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:35.110
just a lie!

62
00:03:37.700 --> 00:03:40.450
Ow...

63
00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:42.490
You lying brat!

64
00:03:42.490 --> 00:03:44.370
You're really gonna get it this time!

65
00:03:47.810 --> 00:03:51.210
Here they come! Here they come!
Here they come! Here they come!

66
00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:53.300
Get back here, you little punk!

67
00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:57.260
Catch me if you can!

68
00:03:58.430 --> 00:04:00.510
Come and get me!

69
00:04:05.430 --> 00:04:08.270
Dammit! He got away again!

70
00:04:09.020 --> 00:04:11.520
He's one hell of a troublemaker!

71
00:04:11.520 --> 00:04:13.650
He's gonna get it when we find him!

72
00:04:14.030 --> 00:04:16.400
Where the hell did he go?!

73
00:04:26.200 --> 00:04:28.080
Another job well done!

74
00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:32.210
I breathed some life into
this boring village!

75
00:04:32.960 --> 00:04:34.090
Ah! There he is!

76
00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:37.220
Oh, it's you guys!

77
00:04:37.760 --> 00:04:40.050
Good morning, Captain Usopp!

78
00:04:40.090 --> 00:04:43.430
Carrot and Pepper
Village Boys

79
00:04:40.300 --> 00:04:43.430
The Usopp Pirates have arrived!

80
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:46.810
Pepper! Carrot!

81
00:04:46.810 --> 00:04:49.440
Just the two of you? Where's Onion?

82
00:04:53.060 --> 00:04:56.650
We're doomed! We're doomed!

83
00:04:56.650 --> 00:04:57.400
Ow!

84
00:04:58.820 --> 00:04:59.990
We're doomed!

85
00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:01.780
Onion...

86
00:05:01.780 --> 00:05:03.870
What's he freaking out about?

87
00:05:03.870 --> 00:05:06.200
We're doomed! We're doomed!

88
00:05:03.910 --> 00:05:09.830
Onion
A Village Boy

89
00:05:06.200 --> 00:05:07.540
We're doomed!

90
00:05:07.540 --> 00:05:09.120
Th-The pirates are coming!

91
00:05:09.120 --> 00:05:12.710
There's a boat with a skull
mark at the north shore!

92
00:05:12.710 --> 00:05:13.750
Yeah, right!

93
00:05:15.920 --> 00:05:17.510
It's the truth!

94
00:05:17.510 --> 00:05:19.760
Th-The truth?

95
00:05:20.090 --> 00:05:22.260
It's true! This is bad!

96
00:05:23.010 --> 00:05:24.510
Oh, crap!

97
00:05:24.510 --> 00:05:26.350
It's time for my snack!

98
00:05:26.350 --> 00:05:27.310
– Don't run away!
– Don't run away!

99
00:05:28.520 --> 00:05:33.560
Actually, I have I'll-die-if-I-
don't-eat-my-snacks disease!

100
00:05:34.730 --> 00:05:36.190
– Liar!
– Liar!

101
00:05:36.820 --> 00:05:40.780
Captain! Don't you wanna
be a real pirate?!

102
00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:44.450
What good is a pirate
who's afraid of pirates?!

103
00:05:44.910 --> 00:05:48.160
If I recall correctly, it was
Buggy the Clown's symbol!

104
00:05:48.160 --> 00:05:52.420
B-B-Buggy the Clown?!

105
00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:56.000
I think I'll just...

106
00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:58.710
But it was just two little boats!

107
00:05:59.710 --> 00:06:02.800
And around three people...

108
00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:08.390
Alright! Let's go, Usopp Pirates!
We must protect our peaceful village!

109
00:06:08.220 --> 00:06:09.140
– Huh?
– Huh?

110
00:06:08.390 --> 00:06:10.850
Okay, let's go! Follow me!

111
00:06:11.850 --> 00:06:13.640
– A-Aye, aye!
– A-Aye, aye!

112
00:06:21.820 --> 00:06:24.820
Finally on dry land again...

113
00:06:26.030 --> 00:06:27.870
There's a village past here?

114
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:28.910
Yeah.

115
00:06:28.910 --> 00:06:31.160
Seems like a small one though...

116
00:06:31.160 --> 00:06:31.790
Oh!

117
00:06:31.790 --> 00:06:34.420
That means there's meat!
Meat, meat, meat!

118
00:06:34.420 --> 00:06:36.290
They've got food, right?!

119
00:06:36.290 --> 00:06:38.380
What is it with you and meat?!

120
00:06:41.050 --> 00:06:42.550
Careful!

121
00:06:42.880 --> 00:06:44.590
We've got company.

122
00:06:43.800 --> 00:06:44.590
Huh?!

123
00:06:44.590 --> 00:06:46.390
Where?! Where?! Where?!

124
00:06:46.970 --> 00:06:48.430
Look out!

125
00:06:59.110 --> 00:07:02.690
That's awesome!

126
00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:02.690
Is this the time to be impressed?!

127
00:07:05.320 --> 00:07:09.700
I am Usopp, leader of the great
pirates who reign over this village!

128
00:07:09.700 --> 00:07:12.910
People praise me—and then they
praise me more—and refer to me as...

129
00:07:13.290 --> 00:07:15.410
Captain Usopp!

130
00:07:17.830 --> 00:07:21.340
If you're thinking of attacking
this village, then forget it!

131
00:07:21.340 --> 00:07:26.550
My 80 million subordinates
won't sit by quietly!

132
00:07:26.550 --> 00:07:31.010
Awesome!

133
00:07:32.390 --> 00:07:33.930
You're lying, aren't you?

134
00:07:34.850 --> 00:07:35.980
She saw through it!

135
00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:38.730
Ah, so you admit it.

136
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:43.690
I admitted it to her!

137
00:07:45.900 --> 00:07:48.240
What?! He was lying?!

138
00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:49.700
Why, you crafty little...!

139
00:07:50.320 --> 00:07:54.660
Eighty million may have been an exaggeration,
but I do have great men under my command!

140
00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:03.800
Like maybe three people?

141
00:08:05.210 --> 00:08:07.260
– She saw through it!
– She saw through it!

142
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:09.970
R-Run!

143
00:08:09.970 --> 00:08:11.970
H-Hey, you guys!

144
00:08:11.970 --> 00:08:14.220
Don't run away!

145
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:17.940
You're hilarious!

146
00:08:18.980 --> 00:08:20.400
Hey, you!

147
00:08:20.400 --> 00:08:21.900
Don't insult me!

148
00:08:21.900 --> 00:08:24.730
I'm a very proud man!

149
00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:28.740
Because of that, people call me...

150
00:08:29.490 --> 00:08:32.200
Proud Usopp!

151
00:08:33.370 --> 00:08:35.080
You saw it yourself just now!

152
00:08:35.450 --> 00:08:40.920
My skill with a slingshot
makes it deadlier than any pistol!

153
00:08:47.800 --> 00:08:50.800
You've drawn your pistol...

154
00:08:50.800 --> 00:08:52.430
so put your life on the line.

155
00:08:54.640 --> 00:08:58.390
I'm saying those are for more
than just threatening someone.

156
00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:20.250
R-Real pirates definitely have way
more punch behind their words...

157
00:09:20.250 --> 00:09:21.620
Incredible...

158
00:09:27.670 --> 00:09:28.760
I stole those lines!

159
00:09:29.880 --> 00:09:33.220
From Shanks, a pirate I look up to.

160
00:09:33.720 --> 00:09:35.970
Sh-Shanks?!

161
00:09:35.970 --> 00:09:39.730
You know the famous pirate
Red-Haired Shanks?!

162
00:09:40.060 --> 00:09:41.230
Yeah!

163
00:09:41.230 --> 00:09:44.150
Your dad's Yasopp, right?

164
00:09:44.150 --> 00:09:46.150
Wh-What?!

165
00:09:51.700 --> 00:09:52.780
Huh?

166
00:09:53.160 --> 00:09:57.910
Yeah, Yasopp is my old man...

167
00:09:59.750 --> 00:10:01.790
But how do you know that?

168
00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:06.340
Village Diner

169
00:10:11.380 --> 00:10:12.800
Good, huh?

170
00:10:14.470 --> 00:10:16.850
I met him when I was a kid!

171
00:10:16.850 --> 00:10:19.560
So my old man's on Shanks' ship?

172
00:10:19.560 --> 00:10:24.560
Yep! You look just like him, so when
I first saw you, it made me wonder...

173
00:10:24.560 --> 00:10:25.560
Really?!

174
00:10:26.310 --> 00:10:29.570
My old man's out there
on an awesome ship?!

175
00:10:29.940 --> 00:10:33.320
I don't know for sure,
but I bet he's still on board.

176
00:10:34.200 --> 00:10:38.280
After all, your dad is
a great sharpshooter!

177
00:10:54.180 --> 00:10:56.640
Awesome!

178
00:10:56.640 --> 00:10:57.640
That's nothing.

179
00:10:57.640 --> 00:11:01.140
I could shoot an ant
right between the eyes!

180
00:11:05.600 --> 00:11:07.350
Y'know, Luffy,

181
00:11:07.350 --> 00:11:11.230
I got a kid named Usopp,
who's just about your age!

182
00:11:11.230 --> 00:11:13.740
You've told me a million
times! I'm sick of it!

183
00:11:13.740 --> 00:11:15.030
What?!

184
00:11:16.700 --> 00:11:19.910
Well, I'm gonna keep tellin' you!

185
00:11:20.660 --> 00:11:24.620
It broke my heart to go,
but I had no choice!

186
00:11:24.620 --> 00:11:29.630
The pirate flag was calling me!
What other reason do you need?!

187
00:11:29.630 --> 00:11:31.340
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

188
00:11:35.170 --> 00:11:38.300
It's stuck! It's stuck!

189
00:11:39.930 --> 00:11:45.060
Usopp, I couldn't tell you how many
times he told me about you.

190
00:11:45.060 --> 00:11:47.270
Yasopp is a great pirate!

191
00:11:47.270 --> 00:11:48.600
Yeah, huh?!

192
00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:55.070
He sailed off into the boundless sea,
living his life on the edge...

193
00:11:55.070 --> 00:11:57.780
I couldn't be more proud of him!

194
00:11:57.780 --> 00:11:59.780
Then that makes this easier!

195
00:12:00.370 --> 00:12:03.580
So, do you know anyone
in the village who can sail?

196
00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:05.700
And provide us with a big ship?

197
00:12:06.910 --> 00:12:09.670
As you can see,
we're just a tiny village...

198
00:12:09.670 --> 00:12:12.800
Sorry, but we can't
live up to your expectations.

199
00:12:12.800 --> 00:12:14.510
At the top of the hill...

200
00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:16.970
there's a huge mansion.

201
00:12:16.970 --> 00:12:19.340
Say! Do you know
the people there, Usopp?!

202
00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:22.220
Could you ask them
to help us pay for one?

203
00:12:22.220 --> 00:12:23.850
Y-You can't go there!

204
00:12:26.100 --> 00:12:29.560
I-I just remembered
something I have to do!

205
00:12:29.560 --> 00:12:32.360
I'm a pretty big deal around here!

206
00:12:32.360 --> 00:12:35.070
So, eat and drink
as much as you want!

207
00:12:35.070 --> 00:12:37.530
Alright! Later!

208
00:12:39.780 --> 00:12:42.450
Why was he in such a hurry?

209
00:12:47.250 --> 00:12:48.710
Is this really the place?!

210
00:12:48.710 --> 00:12:50.870
Yeah, the pirates dragged him inside!

211
00:12:50.870 --> 00:12:52.330
We gotta save him!

212
00:12:52.330 --> 00:12:55.460
But they're real pirates!
Maybe they grilled and ate him!

213
00:12:55.460 --> 00:12:58.090
You idiot! It's witches
that eat people!

214
00:12:59.010 --> 00:13:04.310
This will be the most epic battle since
the formation of the Usopp Pirates!

215
00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:05.560
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

216
00:13:06.810 --> 00:13:09.310
– The Usopp Pirates have arrived!
– The Usopp Pirates have arrived!

217
00:13:09.770 --> 00:13:10.770
Who are they?

218
00:13:10.770 --> 00:13:12.560
Th-The captain is gone!

219
00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:13.650
You don't think he...

220
00:13:14.320 --> 00:13:15.940
H-Hey, pirates!

221
00:13:15.940 --> 00:13:18.650
What'd you do with Captain Usopp?!

222
00:13:18.650 --> 00:13:19.610
– Where is he?!
– Where is he?!

223
00:13:20.110 --> 00:13:22.570
That meat was yummy!

224
00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:24.450
Meat?!

225
00:13:24.450 --> 00:13:26.040
Don't tell me they...

226
00:13:27.660 --> 00:13:30.660
Wh-What?! What did you do?!

227
00:13:30.660 --> 00:13:33.130
If you're looking for your captain...

228
00:13:34.790 --> 00:13:36.090
we ate him.

229
00:13:39.420 --> 00:13:42.760
– A witch!
– A witch!

230
00:13:40.550 --> 00:13:42.760
What're you looking at me for?!

231
00:13:44.720 --> 00:13:47.100
Why'd you go and say
a thing like that?!

232
00:13:53.650 --> 00:13:56.980
Village Mansion

233
00:13:58.480 --> 00:14:00.860
You wish to see Usopp?

234
00:14:01.570 --> 00:14:03.450
Not this again...

235
00:14:03.490 --> 00:14:06.490
Kaya
Mansion Owner

236
00:14:03.860 --> 00:14:04.990
May I?

237
00:14:04.990 --> 00:14:06.490
I want to talk to him.

238
00:14:06.530 --> 00:14:11.790
Klahadore
Mansion Butler

239
00:14:07.990 --> 00:14:09.240
That will not do.

240
00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:11.790
That man is the biggest liar in the village!

241
00:14:12.330 --> 00:14:14.290
In your condition,

242
00:14:14.290 --> 00:14:17.460
Usopp's nonsensical stories
are the last thing you need!

243
00:14:17.460 --> 00:14:21.880
Your late parents entrusted me
with taking care of you...

244
00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:25.220
I must do so to the fullest extent
of my abilities, Miss Kaya.

245
00:14:25.890 --> 00:14:28.560
Now then, I'll leave
your medicine here.

246
00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:30.140
Please be sure to take it.

247
00:14:34.690 --> 00:14:36.020
Jerk.

248
00:14:36.020 --> 00:14:38.190
Call me a "jerk" all you want.

249
00:14:38.190 --> 00:14:40.030
No means no.

250
00:14:50.160 --> 00:14:51.620
Usopp!

251
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:54.620
Hey! You seem as down as ever!

252
00:14:55.120 --> 00:14:56.500
I'm sorry!

253
00:14:56.500 --> 00:14:59.880
I'd really like to invite you in
as a proper guest...

254
00:15:00.630 --> 00:15:04.010
but no matter what,
Klahadore refuses to allow it.

255
00:15:04.010 --> 00:15:05.760
He's not a bad person, though.

256
00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:07.180
Don't sweat it!

257
00:15:07.180 --> 00:15:10.680
I'm a brave warrior
of the sea, after all!

258
00:15:11.060 --> 00:15:15.190
I wouldn't feel at home
in a stuffy mansion.

259
00:15:15.440 --> 00:15:18.440
So what adventure are you going
to tell me about today?

260
00:15:18.440 --> 00:15:21.190
Hmm, let's see...

261
00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:22.480
Alright!

262
00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:23.990
When I was five years old,

263
00:15:23.990 --> 00:15:27.070
I fought a giant goldfish
that lived in the south seas.

264
00:15:27.070 --> 00:15:28.160
A goldfish?

265
00:15:28.410 --> 00:15:29.450
Yeah!

266
00:15:29.450 --> 00:15:31.620
The first thing that shocked me

267
00:15:31.620 --> 00:15:33.290
was the immense size of its poop!

268
00:15:33.290 --> 00:15:37.370
It was so big I made landfall,
thinking it was solid ground.

269
00:15:52.390 --> 00:15:55.520
Whoa! It's huge!

270
00:15:55.520 --> 00:15:58.810
If our captain ran off
at this hour, he'd be here.

271
00:15:58.810 --> 00:16:01.770
Oh? Why would he come here?

272
00:16:01.770 --> 00:16:03.400
To lie!

273
00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:05.070
That's a bad thing!

274
00:16:05.070 --> 00:16:07.780
He's not bad! He's great! Right?!

275
00:16:07.780 --> 00:16:09.160
Yeah! He's great!

276
00:16:09.530 --> 00:16:11.410
How does that work?

277
00:16:12.370 --> 00:16:15.950
Kaya, the girl who lives here, is sick.

278
00:16:13.330 --> 00:16:15.040
A goldfish blocked the ship,

279
00:16:15.040 --> 00:16:19.670
and on that ship was a pirate
taller than a mountain!

280
00:16:15.950 --> 00:16:20.880
And she's been depressed ever since
her parents died from an illness a year ago.

281
00:16:19.670 --> 00:16:22.170
His face was hilarious!

282
00:16:21.420 --> 00:16:25.710
Even all her money can't
change how sad it all is.

283
00:16:26.630 --> 00:16:30.590
Our captain is great at telling
tall tales that make her laugh!

284
00:16:30.930 --> 00:16:34.060
He's the best at telling lies!

285
00:16:34.060 --> 00:16:36.980
Never heard of a pirate with
a face like that, have you?

286
00:16:37.520 --> 00:16:39.480
So, he's a good guy?

287
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:40.690
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

288
00:16:40.690 --> 00:16:44.440
I like the captain because he's nosy!

289
00:16:44.440 --> 00:16:46.940
I like how bossy he is!

290
00:16:46.940 --> 00:16:49.030
I like how boastful he is!

291
00:16:49.400 --> 00:16:52.410
And that helps her feel better?

292
00:16:52.410 --> 00:16:54.030
Yeah, a lot better!

293
00:16:54.030 --> 00:16:55.290
Great!

294
00:16:55.290 --> 00:16:57.870
Let's go ask her for a ship then!

295
00:16:58.330 --> 00:17:00.460
Just getting in is impossible!

296
00:17:00.460 --> 00:17:02.750
The gate guards are really tough!

297
00:17:03.340 --> 00:17:04.040
– Huh?
– Huh?

298
00:17:04.040 --> 00:17:05.050
Where'd Luffy go?

299
00:17:05.050 --> 00:17:06.590
I'll go ask!

300
00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:08.380
Wait, you're not gonna...?!

301
00:17:08.380 --> 00:17:11.130
Gum-Gum...

302
00:17:12.930 --> 00:17:16.390
Sorry...

303
00:17:13.850 --> 00:17:14.760
Hey!

304
00:17:16.390 --> 00:17:20.140
for Barging In!

305
00:17:21.230 --> 00:17:27.820
And then we escaped into the sky
using a gigantic slingshot!

306
00:17:28.530 --> 00:17:30.070
U-Um...

307
00:17:31.490 --> 00:17:33.320
Yahoo!

308
00:17:39.290 --> 00:17:41.080
That worked great!

309
00:17:41.080 --> 00:17:43.290
A-Are you all right?!

310
00:17:43.290 --> 00:17:45.920
Y-Yeah! They're fine! Don't worry!

311
00:17:45.920 --> 00:17:49.170
They heard about me
and traveled all this way

312
00:17:49.170 --> 00:17:51.760
just to join the Usopp Pirates!

313
00:17:52.130 --> 00:17:54.760
Huh? No, we didn't.

314
00:17:55.140 --> 00:17:56.930
We're here to ask a favor!

315
00:17:56.930 --> 00:17:58.560
A favor? Of me?

316
00:17:58.560 --> 00:17:59.390
Yeah!

317
00:17:59.770 --> 00:18:02.890
We want a big ship...

318
00:18:01.270 --> 00:18:02.890
You there!

319
00:18:03.980 --> 00:18:06.110
What is the meaning of this?!

320
00:18:07.610 --> 00:18:09.860
Klahadore...

321
00:18:11.110 --> 00:18:12.860
I don't appreciate you all...

322
00:18:13.860 --> 00:18:16.330
breaking in here without permission!

323
00:18:20.660 --> 00:18:21.790
These people are–

324
00:18:21.790 --> 00:18:22.750
That can wait.

325
00:18:24.210 --> 00:18:27.840
You can tell me your reasoning later.

326
00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:29.840
Now leave, all of you!

327
00:18:29.840 --> 00:18:32.300
Or do you have something to say?

328
00:18:32.670 --> 00:18:35.140
Well, actually, we want a ship!

329
00:18:35.140 --> 00:18:36.260
Absolutely not!

330
00:18:38.060 --> 00:18:39.470
Usopp!

331
00:18:39.470 --> 00:18:40.270
Crap!

332
00:18:40.270 --> 00:18:43.060
I've heard all about you.

333
00:18:43.060 --> 00:18:45.100
You're infamous in the village.

334
00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:47.980
Quite impressive for your age.

335
00:18:47.980 --> 00:18:51.490
Feel free to call me
Captain Usopp, too!

336
00:18:51.490 --> 00:18:53.360
No need for flattery, though!

337
00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:56.950
I've heard stories about
your father as well.

338
00:18:56.950 --> 00:18:57.700
What?!

339
00:18:58.030 --> 00:19:01.370
You're nothing but
the son of a filthy pirate!

340
00:19:02.120 --> 00:19:04.830
I wouldn't put anything past you,

341
00:19:05.170 --> 00:19:09.540
so I ask that you stay away
from the lady of this house!

342
00:19:10.550 --> 00:19:12.630
F-Filthy pirate...?!

343
00:19:13.050 --> 00:19:16.840
You and the lady are from
completely different worlds!

344
00:19:16.840 --> 00:19:18.850
Is it money you're after? How much?

345
00:19:19.260 --> 00:19:22.060
That's enough, Klahadore!
Apologize to Usopp!

346
00:19:23.270 --> 00:19:24.520
Hey, Kaya! Be careful!

347
00:19:25.020 --> 00:19:29.480
What reason is there to apologize
to this savage, my lady?

348
00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:33.320
I am merely stating the truth.

349
00:19:34.190 --> 00:19:36.150
I sympathize with you.

350
00:19:36.150 --> 00:19:39.910
You must truly hate
your idiot of a father

351
00:19:39.910 --> 00:19:42.910
for choosing treasure over
his family and village!

352
00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:44.790
Klahadore!

353
00:19:45.410 --> 00:19:48.040
Don't you dare say
another word about my father!

354
00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:51.290
Usopp!

355
00:19:59.850 --> 00:20:02.390
What are you getting
so worked up about?

356
00:20:02.390 --> 00:20:05.310
Why not simply tell another
one of your outrageous lies?

357
00:20:05.930 --> 00:20:08.770
Tell us how he's actually
a traveling merchant

358
00:20:08.770 --> 00:20:11.310
or that he's not even
your real father...

359
00:20:11.310 --> 00:20:12.860
Shut up!

360
00:20:22.620 --> 00:20:23.830
– Captain!
– Captain!

361
00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:28.580
S-See? Instantly
resorting to violence...!

362
00:20:28.580 --> 00:20:31.420
Like father, like son!

363
00:20:31.420 --> 00:20:33.130
Just shut up!

364
00:20:33.590 --> 00:20:37.090
I'm proud that my father is a pirate!

365
00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:40.840
I'm proud that he's
a brave warrior of the sea!

366
00:20:40.840 --> 00:20:43.890
You're right, I am a liar!

367
00:20:43.890 --> 00:20:48.730
But I'll never lie about my family!
I'm proud of the pirate blood in my veins!

368
00:20:49.100 --> 00:20:51.480
I'm the son of a pirate!

369
00:20:55.610 --> 00:20:56.860
Captain...

370
00:20:59.150 --> 00:21:02.370
A pirate, a brave warrior of the sea?

371
00:21:02.370 --> 00:21:05.410
You'll find any way
to twist the truth...

372
00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:10.670
But you're the undeniable
proof of his savage blood!

373
00:21:10.670 --> 00:21:14.800
You run around spouting lies
and lash out whenever you're angry!

374
00:21:14.800 --> 00:21:18.630
Worst of all, you cozy up to the lady
of the house to steal her fortune!

375
00:21:18.630 --> 00:21:20.300
What?! I just–

376
00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:22.800
The fact that your father is a pirate

377
00:21:22.800 --> 00:21:26.100
is more than enough proof that
you're plotting something!

378
00:21:26.520 --> 00:21:27.850
Shut up already!

379
00:21:27.850 --> 00:21:29.310
Stop, Usopp!

380
00:21:30.600 --> 00:21:33.020
Please, no more violence!

381
00:21:34.440 --> 00:21:37.070
Klahadore isn't a bad person!

382
00:21:37.650 --> 00:21:38.610
He's just...

383
00:21:39.360 --> 00:21:43.160
He's just trying to do
what's best for me!

384
00:21:45.990 --> 00:21:47.410
Leave this place!

385
00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:50.830
Never come near this mansion again!

386
00:21:51.210 --> 00:21:53.040
Yeah, I get it.

387
00:21:53.040 --> 00:21:55.670
You don't have to tell me twice!

388
00:21:57.170 --> 00:21:59.710
I'll never come back here again!

389
00:22:01.090 --> 00:22:02.590
Usopp...

390
00:22:04.220 --> 00:22:06.180
You stupid butt-ler!

391
00:22:06.180 --> 00:22:08.220
Our captain's not that kind of guy!

392
00:22:08.220 --> 00:22:09.720
Yeah! You butthead!

393
00:22:09.720 --> 00:22:10.770
Butthead!

394
00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:12.890
Butthead!

395
00:22:12.890 --> 00:22:15.110
Why are you saying it?

396
00:22:17.940 --> 00:22:22.280
What's your problem?!
Come fight me, if you can!

397
00:22:18.900 --> 00:22:19.940
Stop!

398
00:22:23.150 --> 00:22:25.910
The rest of you will leave as well!

399
00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:40.460
Your meal, my lady.

400
00:22:40.460 --> 00:22:42.260
No thanks.

401
00:22:42.260 --> 00:22:43.630
I've lost my appetite.

402
00:22:47.220 --> 00:22:50.350
The cook would be sad
to hear you say that.

403
00:22:50.350 --> 00:22:55.810
He works his hardest to come up
with meals that suit your needs.

404
00:23:00.820 --> 00:23:02.780
Why did you speak to him like that?

405
00:23:03.650 --> 00:23:10.200
I feel really bad for talking to Usopp
behind your back, Klahadore.

406
00:23:10.200 --> 00:23:13.160
But you didn't need to
kick him out like that.

407
00:23:17.710 --> 00:23:19.500
May I sit?

408
00:23:19.500 --> 00:23:20.340
Go ahead.

409
00:23:22.090 --> 00:23:25.470
It's been nearly three years...

410
00:23:26.470 --> 00:23:29.970
since the day I came to this mansion.

411
00:23:30.680 --> 00:23:34.270
I'll never forget what
happened that day...

412
00:23:43.230 --> 00:23:49.530
I was kicked off the ship I worked on
because of a mistake I made.

413
00:23:49.530 --> 00:23:54.450
And with no work or money, I was
on the verge of dying like a beggar.

414
00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:12.970
In my eyes, I owe my life
to your late parents...

415
00:24:13.430 --> 00:24:18.310
And to you, their daughter.

416
00:24:19.690 --> 00:24:27.030
I realize that it isn't my place
to interfere with your friendships.

417
00:24:27.820 --> 00:24:32.990
But Usopp isn't exactly known
for his upstanding character!

418
00:24:32.990 --> 00:24:37.620
If... by any chance something
should happen to you,

419
00:24:37.620 --> 00:24:41.460
your kind parents
would never forgive me!

420
00:24:42.500 --> 00:24:46.460
Do you think ill of me
for what I did earlier?

421
00:24:46.460 --> 00:24:48.840
No, not at all!

422
00:24:48.840 --> 00:24:51.720
I'm glad to have you too, Klahadore!

423
00:24:51.720 --> 00:24:53.390
But please don't misunderstand.

424
00:24:54.220 --> 00:24:56.680
Usopp is a very nice person.

425
00:24:56.680 --> 00:24:59.980
Still, whether he's
nice or not is irrelevant!

426
00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:01.600
Klahadore!

427
00:25:01.600 --> 00:25:03.310
You blockhead!

428
00:25:03.310 --> 00:25:05.150
Call me a "blockhead" all you want!

429
00:25:09.360 --> 00:25:10.660
Where'd Luffy go?

430
00:25:11.160 --> 00:25:12.280
Who knows?

431
00:25:12.280 --> 00:25:14.580
He probably ran after the "captain."

432
00:25:15.160 --> 00:25:16.830
Our captain would be at his spot!

433
00:25:16.830 --> 00:25:18.540
Yeah, the shore!

434
00:25:18.540 --> 00:25:21.670
He always goes there
when something happens!

435
00:25:21.670 --> 00:25:24.630
Well, never mind that.
Aren't you missing someone?

436
00:25:24.630 --> 00:25:26.760
– Yeah, Onion!
– Yeah, Onion!

437
00:25:26.760 --> 00:25:29.510
He's always running off!

438
00:25:29.510 --> 00:25:32.840
Yeah! And then he
shows up all freaked out!

439
00:25:34.850 --> 00:25:36.310
We're doomed!

440
00:25:36.310 --> 00:25:37.680
See?

441
00:25:37.680 --> 00:25:40.140
There's a backwards guy!

442
00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:43.100
A weird guy is walking
backwards this way!

443
00:25:43.100 --> 00:25:44.230
– Liar!
– Liar!

444
00:25:44.230 --> 00:25:45.770
It's the truth!

445
00:25:45.770 --> 00:25:47.610
Just look!

446
00:25:56.620 --> 00:25:59.580
Hey! Who's calling me weird?!

447
00:25:59.620 --> 00:26:04.630
Jango
A Hypnotist

448
00:26:02.830 --> 00:26:04.630
I'm not weird.

449
00:26:05.710 --> 00:26:07.840
You seem pretty weird to me.

450
00:26:07.840 --> 00:26:09.170
Don't be stupid!

451
00:26:09.170 --> 00:26:11.550
I'm just an ordinary
traveling hypnotist!

452
00:26:11.550 --> 00:26:14.180
H-Hypnotist?! Awesome!

453
00:26:14.180 --> 00:26:15.800
Show us something!

454
00:26:15.800 --> 00:26:17.430
Yeah! Do a trick!

455
00:26:18.060 --> 00:26:19.020
What?!

456
00:26:20.270 --> 00:26:22.270
Don't make me laugh!

457
00:26:22.270 --> 00:26:26.980
Why should I reveal my techniques
to a bunch of strangers?!

458
00:26:27.730 --> 00:26:29.980
Alright. Watch this ring closely.

459
00:26:29.980 --> 00:26:30.990
But you just said...!

460
00:26:31.320 --> 00:26:34.740
You will fall asleep at the count
of "one, two, Jango."

461
00:26:34.740 --> 00:26:35.950
Alright, here we go!

462
00:26:37.080 --> 00:26:38.080
One,

463
00:26:38.080 --> 00:26:39.200
two,

464
00:26:39.200 --> 00:26:39.870
Jango!

465
00:26:43.750 --> 00:26:45.880
Hey! What's this guy's deal?!

466
00:26:50.630 --> 00:26:51.340
Hey!

467
00:26:52.300 --> 00:26:53.550
There you are!

468
00:26:53.550 --> 00:26:56.510
Oh, it's you! Don't just
sneak up like that!

469
00:26:57.100 --> 00:26:59.430
So, what? Do you want something?

470
00:26:59.430 --> 00:27:00.560
Not really.

471
00:27:04.640 --> 00:27:06.480
Ouch...

472
00:27:12.570 --> 00:27:14.450
That damn butler,

473
00:27:14.450 --> 00:27:16.660
insulting my old man like that!

474
00:27:16.660 --> 00:27:19.280
Yeah, I hate that guy too!

475
00:27:19.280 --> 00:27:22.200
No matter what anyone says,
Yasopp is a great pirate!

476
00:27:22.580 --> 00:27:24.040
Yeah, huh?!

477
00:27:24.410 --> 00:27:27.830
In this day and age when
pirates are everywhere,

478
00:27:27.830 --> 00:27:31.710
I'm proud of my old man
for risking his life out at sea!

479
00:27:31.710 --> 00:27:35.260
Yet, that bastard stomped
all over my pride!

480
00:27:35.260 --> 00:27:37.140
He'll pay for this!

481
00:27:37.140 --> 00:27:40.140
So you're not gonna
see that girl anymore?

482
00:27:41.220 --> 00:27:44.100
W-Well, I dunno...

483
00:27:44.100 --> 00:27:47.980
If that butler comes back with
an apology, I might consider it.

484
00:27:47.980 --> 00:27:49.730
You mean that butler?

485
00:27:49.730 --> 00:27:50.480
Yeah...

486
00:27:50.820 --> 00:27:52.570
That butler... That...

487
00:27:52.570 --> 00:27:54.650
What's that butler doing out here?!

488
00:27:54.650 --> 00:27:56.530
H-Hey! Ow, ow!

489
00:27:57.320 --> 00:27:58.570
Hey, Jango.

490
00:27:58.570 --> 00:28:02.080
I told you to keep a low profile.

491
00:28:02.080 --> 00:28:04.370
Yet you were napping
in broad daylight...

492
00:28:04.370 --> 00:28:05.790
Don't be stupid.

493
00:28:05.790 --> 00:28:07.750
I don't stand out one bit.

494
00:28:07.750 --> 00:28:09.080
I'm not weird, either.

495
00:28:09.460 --> 00:28:12.090
There's someone else with him.
Some weird guy...

496
00:28:12.090 --> 00:28:13.710
I've never seen him before.

497
00:28:13.710 --> 00:28:14.840
Who is he?

498
00:28:14.840 --> 00:28:19.050
So, I presume everything is in
place to carry out the plan?

499
00:28:19.050 --> 00:28:20.720
Of course.

500
00:28:24.350 --> 00:28:26.560
We're ready at any moment.

501
00:28:26.940 --> 00:28:29.350
The Mistress Assassination Plan!

502
00:28:32.400 --> 00:28:36.240
A-Assassination?!

503
00:28:41.530 --> 00:28:48.390
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

504
00:28:48.590 --> 00:28:55.410
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

505
00:28:55.660 --> 00:29:02.510
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

506
00:29:02.630 --> 00:29:09.770
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

507
00:29:12.470 --> 00:29:15.150
Look where I am

508
00:29:17.380 --> 00:29:23.560
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

509
00:29:23.900 --> 00:29:30.830
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

510
00:29:30.990 --> 00:29:37.910
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

511
00:29:38.040 --> 00:29:45.040
Take me to the place where memories remain

512
00:29:45.140 --> 00:29:50.910
Please don't ever let them fade
